SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYSunday 3 April S10 V3 Barcelona’s last game was a surprise away demolition of leaders Real Madrid and if they do the same to Sevilla at home today they will move up to second in the LaLiga standings. More details at www.soccer6.co.za M1 Borussia Moenchengladbach vs FSV Mainz 05: Gladbach’s last two German league outings were both 2-0 victories, but they are four points behind Mainz in the Bundesliga standings.M2 Tottenham Hotspur vs Newcastle United: Spurs are chasing a Champions League place and won three of their past four league places. Newcastle put together an eight-match unbeaten run but have since lost twice in a row.M3 Odd vs Tromso: It is the opening weekend of the new league season in Norway. Odd have lost just once at home to Tromso in 19 past visits.M4 Orlando Pirates vs Al Ittihad: Pirates need only a draw to secure top place in the African Confederation Cup group while their Libyan guests can take top place if they win away, leavings the Buccaneers second.M5 Sampdoria vs Roma: Sampdoria have won once in their past seven clashes against Roma, losing four but only one of those at home.M6 Anderlecht vs Sporting Charleroi: Anderlecht have won 41 of 50 past home games against Charleroi with four draws and five defeats.M7 Granada vs Rayo Vallecano: Granada had an away win at Alaves last time out to move out of the La Liga relegation zone. Rayo have not won any of their previous nine fixtures.M8 Juventus vs Inter Milan: Juventus take overtake Inter in the Serie A standings and move into third spot if they win. Juventus are unbeaten in their past 11 home games against Inter.M9 Barcelona vs Sevilla: Barcelona are three points behind Sevilla but if they win will overtake them and move into second spot. Sevilla last won at Camp Nou in 2010.M10 Portland Timbers vs LA Galaxy: Portland have won only one of their opening five games of the Major League Soccer season. Galaxy won their first two but have lost twice since. Suggested permutation:R12.00 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1,2,3 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1,2